data plane is entirely blocked), but it is noteworthy for later validation.\n\nFault Localization\n- Primary faulty element: The SDN controller endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633.\n  - “Connection refused” indicates the IP is reachable but the service is not listening on port 6633 (or is immediately rejecting connections).\n- Secondary affected elements: All three OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) default to dropping traffic due to fail_mode=secure with no controller attachment.\n\nRoot Cause\n- The OpenFlow controller at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting connections on port 6633 (service not running, not listening, or port misconfiguration). As a result, no flows are programmed on the switches, and with fail_mode=secure all traffic is dropped, causing a complete host-to-host connectivity failure.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 18178, "output_tokens": 2778, "total_tokens": 20956, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 17280}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2048}}}
